description.narrative: By 2022, public policies, social protection programmes, and the extreme poverty reduction strategy will have the capacity to monitor investment in children, and respond adequately to the needs of the most vulnerable children, especially adolescent girls., which contributes to Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022 the most vulnerable children and adolescents, and especially girls, will have access to public policies and programmes that promote social inclusion and are supported by Dominican society

description.narrative:
UNICEF strengthened the social protection system to implement the prevention of Child Marriage and Early Unions (CMEU) programme; for the preparedness, response and recovery in emergencies for the most vulnerable children, and for the inclusion of children with disabilities into the social protection programmes. It also strengthened the inter-sectoral coordination of the Social Policy Coordination Cabinet (SPCG) for the Design of the National Plan for the Elimination of CMEU.
Furthermore, it strengthened the national capacities of the Directorate General of Budgets of the Ministry of Finance to carry out measurements of the public investment in children. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:04/02/2020
